abstract: Senator Roy Blunt mixed up Senator Martha McSally with his fellow Missourian, Claire McCaskill, who lost her Senate seat in 2018.
lead_paragraph: Senator Roy Blunt, Republican of Missouri stood up, as his colleagues had, to ask a question. But in rattling off the senators he was teaming up with for the question, he misspoke: Instead of naming Senator Martha McSally, a freshman Republican from Arizona, he named a fellow Missourian, Claire McCaskill, a Democratic senator ousted in 2018.
